==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mannitic
<hw>Man*nit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, resembling, or derived from, mannitol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mannitic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a white
amorphous substance, intermediate between saccharic acid and mannitol,
and obtained by the partial oxidation of the latter.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mannitol</ent>⟦br⟧
